I. Adding the raspberrypi-rt-sv layer to your build
=================================================

--- replace with specific instructions for the raspberrypi-rt-sv layer ---

In order to use this layer, you need to make the build system aware of
it.

Assuming the raspberrypi-rt-sv layer exists at the top-level of your
yocto build tree, you can add it to the build system by adding the
location of the raspberrypi-rt-sv layer to bblayers.conf, along with any
other layers needed. e.g.:

  BBLAYERS ?= " \
    /path/to/yocto/meta \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-poky \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-yocto-bsp \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-raspberrypi-rt-sv \
    "


II. Misc
========

This layer provides PREEMPT-RT and I-pipe/Xenomai kernels for Raspberry Pi.

